Scores of students escaped unhurt on Friday morning as fire razed the post-graduate hostel of the Delta State University (DELSU), Abraka in Ethiope East Local Government Area of Delta State. Reports said the fire started at a section of the building at the wee hours of Friday. Most parts of the two-storey hostel building, specifically the second and third floors, were reportedly destroyed before the inferno was checked by fire servicemen of the institution. Fuel loaded tanker razed by fire in Onitsha, no casualty ―… BREAKING: Fire ravages houses, shops at Akala Express area… Fire guts Lagos building Fire guts power plants in Ondo ALSO READ: Philip Morris Nigeria officially recognised as Top Employer 2020 The fire was attributed to an electrical fault which ignited the fire on the second floor of the building. While some property of some of the students were reportedly destroyed, it was gathered that no life was lost in the incident. Confirming the incident, the DELSU Public Relations Officer, Mr Eddy Agbure, described the damage to the building as huge but expressed gratitude that no life was lost. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.